This is an example of the Enter Payment page for multiple recipients when it is filled out. All the recipients selected on the
Select Recipient page will have their own payment card on this page. Each payment here is paid from the same account
selected at the top of the page. If there is only one Paid From account for the OU, this field will be pre-populated.
The total section shows the sum of all the payment amount on each card to inform user of the total amount being
paid to recipients. As the user adds and removes payment cards, the total will be reflected accordingly in real time.
If there are more than one Recipient Account associated with this recipient, the user will be able to select the
dropdown and pick the account they wish to make this payment. These accounts are added to the recipient profile in
the Recipient Creation flow (see DBank_RecipientMangement_DD file for more details).
Here is an example of when the card is completely filled out. Only the Amount field and Recipient Account fields are
required here. All other fields are optional.
If additional information has been added to the payment through the Remittance Information flow by clicking on ‘Add’
text link (see DBank_RemittanceInformation_DD file for more details), the documents will be visible on this table
here. The user can click on each line item on this table which will open an overlay, to view the document details.
There are a maximum of 5 documents that can be add to a single payment. There are no restrictions on the
document types that can be added; duplicates are permitted. Once the user reaches the maximum number of
